{"slug":"sirkuler-25-0239eng","reference":"Sirkuler_25_0239ENG","gazette":"General Directorate of Customs","title":"There is no need for a permit for importing Turkish origin electric vehicles produced in the free zone","date":"17 Mart 2025","bodyHtml":"<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 1rem; outline: 0px !important;\">Communiqué on the Importation of Certain Electric Vehicles (Import: 2023/22) was published in the Official Gazette dated 29/11/2023 and numbered 32384. In the importation of electric vehicles within the scope of the said Communiqué that do not originate from the European Union or countries with which a Free Trade Agreement has been signed, a \"Permit Certificate\" issued by the Ministry of Industry and Technology or the institution or organization authorized by it is required.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 1rem; outline: 0px !important;\">As a result of the evaluations made by the Ministry regarding electric vehicles produced in the Free Zone and of Turkish origin, the companies operating in the Free Zones;</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 1rem; outline: 0px !important;\">- Having been operating in Free Zones before the date of the first publication of the Communiqué (29.11.2023),</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 1rem; outline: 0px !important;\">- Electric vehicle production was included among the production activities before the first publication date of the Communiqué (29.11.2023),</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 1rem; outline: 0px !important;\">- Providing the conditions for gaining Turkish origin for the produced electric vehicles</p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 1rem; outline: 0px !important;\">If the conditions are met and the necessary supporting documents are submitted to the relevant Customs Administration, the customs entry declarations of the vehicles in question (Free Circulation Regime) will be registered and their import will be permitted without the \"Permit Certificate\" specified in the relevant Communiqué, with the Approval of the Ministry dated 28/02/2025.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; text-align: center; line-height: normal; outline: 0px !important;\"><b style=\"outline: 0px !important;\"><span times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt\"=\"\" style=\"font-size: 11pt; outline: 0px !important; font-weight: 400 !important;\"><font style=\"vertical-align: inherit; outline: 0px !important;\"><font style=\"vertical-align: inherit; outline: 0px !important;\">TR</font></font><o:p style=\"outline: 0px !important;\"></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; text-align: center; line-height: normal; outline: 0px !important;\"><b style=\"outline: 0px !important;\"><span times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt\"=\"\" style=\"font-size: 11pt; outline: 0px !important; font-weight: 400 !important;\"><font style=\"vertical-align: inherit; outline: 0px !important;\"><font style=\"vertical-align: inherit; outline: 0px !important;\">MINISTRY OF COMMERCE</font></font><o:p style=\"outline: 0px !important;\"></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; text-align: center; line-height: normal; outline: 0px !important;\"><b style=\"outline: 0px !important;\"><span times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt\"=\"\" style=\"font-size: 11pt; outline: 0px !important; font-weight: 400 !important;\"><font style=\"vertical-align: inherit; outline: 0px !important;\"><font style=\"vertical-align: inherit; outline: 0px !important;\">General Directorate of Customs</font></font><o:p style=\"outline: 0px !important;\"></o:p></span></b></p><p 